2018 has been filled with travel, lots of work, blessings, growth, and all things happy. I also experienced some loss and other things, but ain’t nobody got time for negative things because those only lead to the aforementioned “growth”....2019 will be a continuation of all things positive and continuing to live my best life. It’s about finding new ways to pay it forward, show gratitude, be a better man, son, student of life, musician, employee, friend, etc. I’m trying to be healthier, happier, and sexier in 2019 and beyond. I’m thankful for the people in my life. Thankful for the losses. Thankful for the gains. Thankful the knowledge. Thankful for the experiences. Thankful to God almighty for all things. I’m ready for more and to work harder than ever. Let’s go! To encapsulate all of what I just said, here’s a photo of me in Iceland that has nothing to do with what I just talked about, but I think I look good in it. Amen. 😂 One love! Oh and be on the lookout for my album cause that’s gonna be flames. Ok bye. .

Of all pictures that I’ve taken this year, this is absolutely my favorite one. My dad and I roughly the same age, two decades apart. Taken in Jamaica at my late great grandmother’s home, on the same limb of the same coconut tree in the backyard. The place my father grew up, and where I spent so much time as a kid. My Great Grandmother was a straight up G and babied the crap out of me. I swear I always miss her and will forever cherish those memories. Anyway, my dad is a pretty cool dude and I am so appreciative of growing up with this guy. I’m appreciative of how close we’ve gotten over time and I love this dude times a million. Anyway , it’s late and I don’t sleep, but here’s a little sneak peak into some Jamaican Nostalgia. I played on this tree and drank so many coconuts from this same tree for years! .

.
